---
/**
 * Standards & compliance — the trust block.
 *
 * For a B2B sale into councils and inspection companies, the buyer's first
 * question after "does it work?" is "is it defensible?". This section
 * answers that without overclaiming.
 *
 * Four pillars: standards, certifications context, data residency, security.
 * Phrased as facts about the product, not boasts.
 */
---

<section class="border-b border-brand-100 bg-brand-900 text-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-100">
        Standards & compliance
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
        Built to the standard your work is judged by.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-brand-100">
        Designed for UK inspectors and the organisations that commission them.
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl class="mx-auto mt-16 grid max-w-5xl gap-10 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">

      <div>
        <dt class="text-base font-semibold">
          
            href="/bs-en-1176"
            class="group inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-white transition hover:text-brand-100"
          >
            BS EN 1176
            <svg
              class="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-brand-100">
          Report templates for routine, operational, and annual inspections
          aligned with the standard&apos;s structure and terminology.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="text-base font-semibold">
          
            href="/rpii"
            class="group inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-white transition hover:text-brand-100"
          >
            For RPII inspectors
            <svg
              class="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-brand-100">
          Built around the workflow of certified inspectors in the field —
          not retrofitted from a generic asset-management tool.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="text-base font-semibold text-white">UK data residency</dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-brand-100">
          All data stored on infrastructure in the UK. Encrypted at rest and
          in transit. UK GDPR compliant.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="text-base font-semibold text-white">Audit-ready</dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-brand-100">
          Every report timestamped and tied to its inspector. Photo evidence
          embedded. Findings carried forward inspection to inspection.
        </dd>
      </div>

    </dl>
  </div>
</section>
